<h2>Why Med Spa SEO Matters More Than Ads</h2>
<p>Paid ads deliver immediate traffic. SEO delivers compounding traffic. The difference matters more for med spas than most industries.</p>
<h3>The Cost Problem with Ads</h3>
<p>Med spa keywords are expensive. "Botox near me" costs $5 to $12 per click on Google Ads. "Laser hair removal [city]" runs $4 to $8. A med spa spending $3,000 per month on ads might generate 300 to 500 clicks. At a 5% conversion rate, that is 15 to 25 new patient inquiries.</p>
<p>The same budget invested in SEO content and local optimization produces results that last. A service page ranking for "Botox in [city]" generates free clicks every month. After 6 months, you have 6 pages ranking. After 12 months, 12 pages. The traffic compounds while the cost stays flat.</p>
<h3>The Local Search Opportunity</h3>
<p>Med spas are hyperlocal businesses. Patients search for treatments within driving distance. That makes local SEO the highest-ROI channel available.</p>
<p><a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile optimization</a> drives Map Pack visibility. Service pages target treatment-specific keywords. Reviews build trust signals. Together, these three elements create a local search presence that paid ads cannot replicate.</p>
<h3>What Competitors Get Wrong</h3>
<p>Most med spa SEO advice focuses on broad tactics: "optimize your website" or "post on social media." That advice is too generic to execute. This guide gives you the exact structure, keywords, and process for each element of med spa SEO.</p>
