<h3>Long-Tail Keywords That Convert</h3>
<p>Long-tail keywords have lower volume but higher intent. A patient searching "how much does CoolSculpting cost in Phoenix" is closer to booking than someone searching "body contouring."</p>
<p>Use Google autocomplete to find these. Type your treatment name and note every suggestion. Each suggestion is a proven keyword with real search volume.</p>
<p><strong>Examples:</strong>
- "Botox for forehead lines cost [city]"
- "best lip filler for thin lips [city]"
- "laser hair removal Brazilian [city]"
- "how many units of Botox for crow's feet"
- "microneedling before and after acne scars"</p>
<p>Target these long-tail keywords in <a href="/blog/keyword-research-for-blog-posts/">blog posts</a> and FAQ sections on your service pages.</p>
