<h2>Technical SEO for Med Spa Websites</h2>
<p>Technical SEO ensures Google can crawl, index, and rank your pages. Most med spa websites have fixable issues that hold them back.</p>
<h3>Mobile Optimization</h3>
<p>Over 70% of med spa searches happen on mobile devices. If your site is not mobile-friendly, you lose both rankings and patients.</p>
<p><strong>Mobile checklist:</strong>
- [ ] Pages load in under 3 seconds on mobile
- [ ] Text is readable without zooming
- [ ] Buttons and links are large enough to tap
- [ ] Images resize correctly on smaller screens
- [ ] No horizontal scrolling required
- [ ] Booking forms work on mobile</p>
<p>Use Google PageSpeed Insights to test your site. Fix anything scoring below 80 on mobile. <a href="/blog/improve-core-web-vitals/">Core Web Vitals</a> are a confirmed ranking factor. Slow pages rank lower.</p>
<h3>Schema Markup</h3>
<p><a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">Schema markup</a> helps Google understand your content. For med spas, 3 types matter most:</p>
<p><strong>LocalBusiness schema:</strong> Tells Google your name, address, phone, hours, and service area. Required for strong local SEO.</p>
<p><strong>MedicalBusiness schema:</strong> A more specific type that identifies your business as a healthcare provider. Adds credibility signals.</p>
<p><strong>FAQPage schema:</strong> Turns your FAQ sections into rich results in Google search. More SERP real estate means more clicks.</p>
<p>Add schema to every service page and your homepage. Use JSON-LD format. Most website builders support it through plugins or custom code.</p>
<h3>Site Structure and Internal Linking</h3>
<p>A clean site structure helps Google crawl your pages efficiently.</p>
<p><strong>Recommended med spa site structure:</strong></p>
<pre><code>Homepage
├── Services (hub page)
│   ├── Botox
│   ├── Lip Filler
│   ├── CoolSculpting
│   ├── Microneedling
│   └── [Each treatment]
├── About
├── Before &amp; After Gallery
├── Blog
│   ├── Treatment articles
│   ├── Cost/comparison articles
│   └── Seasonal content
├── Contact / Book Now
└── Locations (if multi-location)
</code></pre>
<p>Link related service pages to each other. Link blog posts to relevant service pages. This internal linking structure distributes authority across your site and helps Google understand the relationship between your content.</p>
<h3>HTTPS and Security</h3>
<p>Your site must use HTTPS. Google flags non-HTTPS sites as "Not Secure." For a healthcare business handling patient inquiries, that warning destroys trust instantly.</p>
<p>If your site still runs on HTTP, contact your hosting provider. Most offer free SSL certificates through Let's Encrypt.</p>
